title: Jack Lehane
text:
John Lehane (1884 - 18 August 1938) was an <a href="Irish%20people">Irish</a> <a href="Gaelic%20football">Gaelic football</a>er who played as a forward for the <a href="Cork%20GAA">Cork</a> senior team.
Kelleher made his first appearance for the team during the <a href="All-Ireland%20Senior%20Football%20Championship%201907">1907 championship</a> and was a regular member of the starting fifteen for a number of seasons. During that time he won one <a href="All-Ireland%20Senior%20Football%20Championship">All-Ireland</a> medal and two <a href="Munster%20Senior%20Football%20Championship">Munster</a> medals.
At club level Lehane was a multiple <a href="Cork%20Senior%20Football%20Championship">county championship</a> medalist with <a href="Macroom%20GAA">Macroom</a>.
